    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>carrot</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>shallot</strong> and cook for 3 min</p><p>Add your <strong>curry powder</strong> and cook for a further 2 min</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the vegetables evenly</p>",
